I at least got pity laughs.

00:27.561 --> 00:29.527
- I won't be doing that.
- Hmm.

00:29.529 --> 00:31.162
Well, this'll be fun then.

00:31.164 --> 00:33.665
Um, I'm gonna go, and maybe
once you've read that,

00:33.667 --> 00:35.099
- you can call me.
- Sit.

00:35.101 --> 00:37.569
Okay.

00:37.571 --> 00:40.171
I can't help but notice inconsistencies

00:40.173 --> 00:41.706
in your treatment.

00:41.708 --> 00:46.244
Missed chemo sessions,
erratic radiation schedule.

00:46.246 --> 00:47.745
That won't work.

00:47.747 --> 00:49.681
Virginia, I've never seen you
with a patient before,

00:49.683 --> 00:51.516
but I gotta say, very impressed.

00:51.518 --> 00:54.052
This whole scary-principal
thing you got going on,

00:54.054 --> 00:55.220
it's very effective.

00:55.222 --> 00:57.355
But I am not your normal patient

00:57.357 --> 01:00.692
because I have a huge hospital to run,

01:00.694 --> 01:03.461
and so when it comes to things
like scheduling,

01:03.463 --> 01:05.363
I gotta keep it flexible.

01:05.364 --> 01:07.131
But you learn to love it.

01:08.368 --> 01:11.102
Radiation is set
for this afternoon, 2:00 p.m.

01:11.104 --> 01:13.705
Great. See? Easy.

01:13.707 --> 01:15.607
As long as there's no hospital emergency,

01:15.609 --> 01:16.808
then I will see you there.

01:16.810 --> 01:18.576
Max, you are the emergency.

01:18.578 --> 01:21.045
Radiation is set
for this afternoon, 2:00 p.m.

01:21.047 --> 01:22.614
2:00 p.m., I heard you. But listen.

01:22.616 --> 01:24.782
- I...
- No, you start listening.

01:26.386 --> 01:29.387
Your treatment's impact is cumulative.

01:29.389 --> 01:31.489
Your brain is going to operate

01:31.491 --> 01:33.658
at half the capacity you're used to.

01:33.660 --> 01:36.094
You're going to be in a lot of pain.

01:36.096 --> 01:38.630
And that is if the treatment is working,

01:38.632 --> 01:40.498
But you're not letting it work. Why?

01:40.500 --> 01:43.879
Why? Because I have
a million things to do.

01:43.881 --> 01:45.403
I have a child on the way.

01:45.405 --> 01:47.105
If I'm too far gone by the time
it gets here...

01:47.107 --> 01:49.173
Dr. Sharpe said you'd make excuses.

01:49.175 --> 01:51.075
Did she? Really?

01:51.077 --> 01:54.345
- It's time to get ready, Max.
- Yeah, for what?

01:54.347 --> 01:57.115
To step down as medical director.

02:02.188 --> 02:03.288
We'll see about that.

02:05.458 --> 02:09.294
Synced & corrected by -robtor-
www.addic7ed.com

02:09.295 --> 02:10.762
Hang in there, Lyn.

02:10.764 --> 02:12.597
- Doctor?
- What you got?

02:12.599 --> 02:14.499
An overprotective dad-to-be
who needs to chill out.

02:14.501 --> 02:16.334
Her back's been sore and
she's had these awful headaches

02:16.336 --> 02:17.802
and she's, like, forgetting things.

02:17.804 --> 02:19.270
She nearly fainted at the coffee shop.

02:19.272 --> 02:20.605
It's called having a baby, Michael.

02:20.607 --> 02:22.273
- Vitals?
- Found them right outside.

02:22.275 --> 02:23.474
- We didn't have time.
- All right, we got it.

02:23.476 --> 02:25.476
Thanks. How far along are you?

02:25.478 --> 02:27.545
- 39 weeks.
- Do you have a birth plan?

02:27.547 --> 02:29.380
- Yeah.
- Any allergies?

02:29.382 --> 02:30.782
- No.
- Complications?

02:30.784 --> 02:32.450
Just having these really bad headaches.

02:32.452 --> 02:34.452
Mom's blood pressure: 290/160.

02:34.454 --> 02:37.622
Heart rate 130 and fetal heart
rate 90 and falling.

02:37.624 --> 02:39.123
All right. Trauma One.

02:39.125 --> 02:40.224
We have to do an emergency C-section.

02:40.226 --> 02:41.292
Call OB, but I'm not waiting.

02:41.294 --> 02:42.694
- What, now?
- What?

02:42.696 --> 02:43.795
- What's happening?
- Is the baby okay?

02:43.797 --> 02:45.330
- Michael?
- Just breathe.

02:45.332 --> 02:46.898
- Michael!
- Should I call her doctor?

02:50.337 --> 02:51.869
Clamps and forceps, please.

02:51.871 --> 02:54.205
We won't need the Metz.
Get them off the tray.

02:54.207 --> 02:55.707
- Your name's Michael Archer?
- Uh, yes.

02:55.709 --> 02:57.208
Lift your arms.

02:57.210 --> 02:58.476
Turn around.

02:58.478 --> 03:00.478
Your date of birth is May 28th, 1988?

03:00.480 --> 03:02.513
Patient intubated and sedated.

03:02.515 --> 03:03.848
How we doing?

03:03.850 --> 03:06.250
- Almost prepped...
- Guys, please.

03:06.252 --> 03:07.819
- I need to be in there.
- I need you to lift your foot.

03:07.821 --> 03:09.420
What are the last four digits
of your social?

03:09.422 --> 03:12.724
- Uh, 0501.
- 0501.

03:12.726 --> 03:14.192
And the other foot.

03:14.194 --> 03:15.660
Fetal heart rate still falling.

03:15.662 --> 03:17.228
Preparing to sterilize incision site.

03:17.230 --> 03:18.830
Let's go.

03:18.832 --> 03:20.665
You cannot touch anything in
there unless we say it's okay.

03:20.667 --> 03:22.166
- You got it?
- Yeah.

03:22.168 --> 03:23.935
Okay. Let's go.

03:26.506 --> 03:29.207
- PGA and polyglactin 910.
- Is she okay?

03:29.209 --> 03:30.742
She's sedated to help
with the hypertension,

03:30.744 --> 03:32.210
but we need to get your baby out now

03:32.212 --> 03:33.511
for both of their sakes. Protractor.

03:33.513 --> 03:34.912
- Richardson.
- Where's OB?

03:34.914 --> 03:36.347
Okay, need a little help here.

03:36.349 --> 03:37.582
- Is everything okay?
- Got it?

03:37.584 --> 03:38.750
Okay, hold it nice and wide for me.

03:38.752 --> 03:40.251
What's wrong? Doctor?

03:40.253 --> 03:42.353
- The cord?
- I'm trying.

03:42.355 --> 03:43.721
- Doctor.
- Suction.

03:43.723 --> 03:45.690
Just a little more.

03:48.528 --> 03:53.531
Time of birth, 10:23 a.m.
You have a strong baby boy.

03:59.639 --> 04:01.472
Give me those Apgar scores.

04:01.474 --> 04:02.974
- Yes, doctor.
- All right, I see that.

04:05.879 --> 04:09.380
Birth weight, uh, 7.6 pounds.

04:09.382 --> 04:12.550
Apgar of nine. He's very healthy.

04:12.552 --> 04:15.453
Let's close her up.

04:15.455 --> 04:17.255
How's Lyn? She okay?

04:17.257 --> 04:19.457
No signs of hemorrhaging
or excess bleeding.

04:19.459 --> 04:21.892
She's still hypertensive.

04:21.894 --> 04:23.726
Wanna hold him, Daddy?

04:24.564 --> 04:27.498
There you go. Support his head.

04:30.603 --> 04:32.276
Hi, Robin.

04:33.006 --> 04:34.672
Hey, there!

04:36.910 --> 04:39.577
- Ta-da.
- You amaze me.

04:39.579 --> 04:41.779
I wear paper very well.

04:41.781 --> 04:43.581
I'm not talking about how you look.

04:43.583 --> 04:45.016
I'm talking about how
you're tackling this.

04:45.018 --> 04:48.019
All by yourself. Freezing your eggs.

04:48.021 --> 04:49.620
Lots of women do.

04:49.622 --> 04:51.756
Lots of women aren't chair of oncology.

04:53.460 --> 04:55.526
I knew there was a reason I invited you.

05:00.266 --> 05:01.833
So, that nurse earlier,

05:01.835 --> 05:03.434
thinking I was here to fertilize...

05:03.436 --> 05:05.937
Oh, my God. I mean, can you imagine?

05:05.939 --> 05:07.438
We've only been together a month.

05:07.440 --> 05:10.708
So awkward. So awkward.

05:12.545 --> 05:15.613
That said, I...

05:15.987 --> 05:19.817
I know the biological
pressure you're under.

05:19.819 --> 05:22.687
So what if...

05:22.689 --> 05:26.057
- That's not a reason to...
- No, no, of course not.

05:26.059 --> 05:31.043
I just, um... here I am, able to help.

05:31.831 --> 05:34.999
- Not helping feels...
- No, yeah.

05:35.001 --> 05:36.534
I get it.

05:37.971 --> 05:39.837
I mean, I have thought about it.

05:39.839 --> 05:41.472
- You have?
- Oh, no.

05:41.474 --> 05:42.974
I mean, I've... I've thought about it,

05:42.976 --> 05:44.308
but I haven't, like, thought about it.

05:44.310 --> 05:45.543
Right.

05:45.545 --> 05:46.811
Yeah, it's just a lot to put on this

05:46.813 --> 05:48.579
and on us at this time.

05:48.581 --> 05:50.815
- Hopefully we'll get there.
- Yeah.

05:53.686 --> 05:55.419
I just don't wanna lose our chance.

05:58.925 --> 06:02.393
It's E-day, Helen. Ready to go?

06:06.599 --> 06:12.251
Um, actually, I think I just
need a little bit more time.

06:12.672 --> 06:15.106
You can have till 5:00 p.m.

06:15.108 --> 06:17.575
Any longer, we'll miss our
chance to retrieve

06:17.577 --> 06:19.844
any eggs at all, fertilized or not.

06:21.447 --> 06:22.780
I'll see you at five?

